condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :PA, Section I, para 5 | Description :Each PIE shall ensure the project is carried out in accordance with theprovisions of the Anti-corruption Guidelines. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Section I, para 8 | Description :Each PIE shall ensure that forestland use certificates will be issued tofarmers and or farmer groups in a timely manner and will cover the project areas indicated in the Project Agreement. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement: PA, Section I, para 1 (a)(b) | Description :The Project Implementing Entity (PIE) shall maintain till thecompletion of the project the provincial, municipal and county level Project leading Groups and PMOs. | Frequency: Yearly

Finance Agreement: PA, Section I, para 2 | Description :Each PIE shall prepare an annual work and budget plan for the next calendaryear by Dec 15 of each year, and ensure project activities are in accordance with these plans. | Frequency: Yearly

Finance Agreement: PA, Section I, para 3 (a)(b) | Description :Each PIE shall apply the measures and actions set forth in the EMPand the EMDP, and not amend, suspend or waive any of these planswithout prior agreement with the Bank. | Frequency: Quarterly
Finance Agreement: PA, Section I, para 4 (a)(b) | Description :Each PIE shall apply the implementation of the PIP in the mannersatisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency: Quarterly
Finance Agreement: PA, Section II, para A,2 | Description :Each PIE shall prepare a mid-term report. | Due Date: 31-Mar-2013
